author: sviens
msg: Applied patch from issue JUDDI-54.  When saving a Business or Service.  New ServiceKey and BindingKey values were were being generated and used when they should not have been.  These values should only be generated when saving new Services or Bindings.

author: sviens
msg: jUDDI Proxy no longer allows directly specifying the SOAP implementation to use

author: sviens
msg: RegistryProxy no longer requires that a Transport implementation be specified.  It will used Axis excluslively (for now).  This is the first step in moving away from the need to specify ANY soap implementation.  Next step will be to use the javax.xml.soap (SAAJ) classes and remove any reference to axis classes.

author: sviens
msg: Turned off Log4j debugging. Log4j will no longer send debug statements to System.out.
